-- Brazil Congress Chief Takes Official Jet to Wedding, Folha Says
-- B y   R a y m o n d   C o l i t t
-- 2013-07-04T13:32:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-04/brazil-congress-chief-takes-official-jet-to-wedding-folha-says.html
Head of Brazil’s Senate, Renan
Calheiros, traveled on Air Force plane paid for with tax money
to attend private wedding ceremony June 15, Folha de  Sao Paulo 
 reports  today.
* By law, authorities can use Air Force planes only on official
trips, in medical emergencies or for security reasons, Folha
says
* A spokesman for Calheiros didn’t return phone messages
requesting comment
* NOTE: Incident comes after more than 1 million people in June
protested against corruption and for better public services
* NOTE: Head of lower house of Congress, Henrique Eduardo Alves,
used Air Force plane to take family members to see Brazil beat
 Spain  in a weekend soccer final in  Rio de Janeiro , Folha
reported yesterday. Alves said he had an official lunch that day
with the mayor of Rio and will reimburse public coffers for cost
of commercial plane ticket for seven family members and friends
who accompanied him, Folha reported
* NOTE: Alves and Calheiros are leading efforts in Congress to
make  Brazil ’s political system more transparent, representative,
less susceptible to corruption
